f=Engineering/dana/custom/migration-discipline/SKILL.md · in=migration-discipline Security Charter Rail becomes concrete workflow: **dana authors schema/data change prepared, reversible, reviewable script operator runs it.** agent, dana included, executes create/update/delete/drop/truncate migration. migration ships down-script tested first, sequenced deploy stays independently rollback-able (ops's expand-migrate-contract). · p=agent silently mutate drop business data single catastrophic failure mode charter exists prevent data analogue "never move money." skill makes destructive data changes human construction: dana produces script plain-language summary what does; operator reads, approves, runs it. Reversibility mandatory because one irreversible migration one you desperately need undo. · wu=Triggers: "migrate," "schema change," "add/drop column," "alter table," "backfill," "data fix," any create/update/delete/drop/truncate scale, standing new store (datastore-selection's handoff). · st:/ Protocol=`A schema/data change is needed \· -> dana AUTHORS the migration script (assets/migration-script-template.md): \· up-script \· DOWN-script (reversible) \· plain-language effect summary \· affected rows/tables estimate \· -> Sequence: expand → migrate → contract (additive first; each step independently rollback-able) \· -> DOWN-script TESTED (against a scratch/restored copy) BEFORE the up runs — untested down = not done` · in=**dana writes; operator runs. Always.** migration prepared script plus plain-language summary effect. dana hands operator stops. configuration, urgency, environment dana executes destructive data change Rail hard rule (charter: "not configurable"). **Reversible isn't done.** up-script tested down-script. irreversible change genuine data transform can't undone) requires explicit operator sign-off before authoring, written recovery plan place down-script, risk entry never silent one-way door (mirrors ops's release-discipline). **Test down before up.** rollback exercised against scratch restored copy first because down-script never run exactly trustworthy backup never restored (ops's rule). Untested reversibility fails gate. **Sequence expand-migrate-contract.** Additive changes first (new column/edge, nullable), code uses old new shapes, contraction later. keeps deploy independently rollback-able (ops's sequencing) avoids mid-migration state neither old new code works. **The summary human.** plain-language effect summary "adds nullable `status` column `orders`, backfills ~2.3M rows 'legacy', drops nothing" what operator approves against. script operator can't understand isn't ready; summary optional. **Verify after, feed system.** After operator runs it, dana verifies result matches summary's expectation, migration becomes part ops's deploy record quinn's gate evidence. migration something summary incident (ops). · of=`## Migration: [name] — [store] \· Effect (plain language): [what it does, tables/rows affected, what it does NOT touch] \· Up-script: [ref] \· Down-script: [ref] \· Down TESTED on scratch/restore: ✓ [evidence] \· Sequence: expand / migrate / contract — this step independently rollback-able: ✓ \· Rail 3: authored by dana \· TO BE RUN BY OPERATOR (dana does not execute)` · pr=**dana writes, operator runs always** (Rail configurable, urgency exception)., **Reversible done** tested down-script, explicit operator sign-off recovery plan true one-way changes., **Test down before up** unexercised rollback rollback., **Expand-migrate-contract** deploy stays independently reversible., **The summary human** operator approves plain language, opaque SQL., **Verify after** migration diverged summary incident. · f=scratch/restore environment test down test against production-shaped local copy, label gap infrastructure debt (ops); never skip down-test., Genuinely irreversible change operator sign-off BEFORE authoring written recovery plan risk entry; reversibility requirement replaced explicit human acceptance, never waived silently., Urgent data fix mid-incident STILL prepared script operator runs (incident-response's rule); urgency classic cover exact breach Rail stops., Operator unavailable migration waits; dana run "unblock." blocked migration exception Rail · b:with Other Skills=**charter/Rail 3**: skill Rail 3's authoring workflow; quinn's charter-enforcement verifies agent-executed destructive ever occurs., **datastore-selection** (sibling) chooses store; stands moves data it., **data-modeling** (sibling) designs schema migration changes; **db-performance** (sibling) reviews index changes migration includes., **ops/release-discipline**: consumes migrations deploy sequencing (expand-migrate-contract, operator-run); migration part deploy record., **quinn**: migrations locked plan scanned Rail compliance; operator-run path verified, assumed.